    <div id="reviews-list">
        {% for review in reviews %}
            <div class="review-card">
                <h3>{{ review.dish_name }}</h3>
                <p>Rating: {{ review.rating }} stars</p>
                <p>{{ review.review_text }}</p>
                <p>Date: {{ review.review_date }}</p>
            </div>
            <hr>
        {% else %}
            <p>No reviews found.</p>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <button id="write-new-review-button" onclick="location.href='{{ url_for('write_review') }}'">Write New Review</button>
    <button id="back-to-dashboard" onclick="location.href='{{ url_for('dashboard') }}'">Back to Dashboard</button>
</div>
</body>
</html>
```

templates/write_review.html
```html
'''
Write Review page template for RestaurantReservation.
Form to write a review for a dish.
Uses Flask url_for for navigation.
'''
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Write Review</title>
</head>
<body>
<div id="write-review-page">
    <h1>Write Review</h1>
    <form method="post" action="{{ url_for('write_review') }}">
        <label for="select-dish">Select Dish:</label>
        <select id="select-dish" name="select-dish" required>
            {% for dish in menu %}
                <option value="{{ dish.dish_id }}">{{ dish.name }}</option>
            {% endfor %}
        </select><br><br>

        <label for="rating-input">Rating:</label>
        <select id="rating-input" name="rating-input" required>
            {% for i in range(1,6) %}
                <option value="{{ i }}">{{ i }} star{{ 's' if i > 1 else '' }}</option>
            {% endfor %}
        </select><br><br>

        <label for="review-text">Review:</label><br>
        <textarea id="review-text" name="review-text" rows="5" cols="50" required></textarea><br><br>

        <button id="submit-review-button" type="submit">Submit Review</button>
    </form>
    <button id="back-to-reviews" onclick="location.href='{{ url_for('my_reviews') }}'">Back to My Reviews</button>
</div>
</body>
</html>
```

