### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a web framework (e.g., Flask). 
  It handles routing, page rendering, form submissions, data reading/writing to local text files, and business logic for all nine pages.

- templates/
  Directory containing HTML template files for each page of the web application. Each file corresponds to one of the nine pages described:
    - dashboard.html: Dashboard page layout and elements.
    - menu.html: Menu page with dish listings and filtering.
    - dish_details.html: Detailed dish information page.
    - make_reservation.html: Reservation form page.
    - my_reservations.html: User's reservations listing page.
    - waitlist.html: Waitlist management page.
    - my_reviews.html: User's reviews listing page.
    - write_review.html: Form page to write a new review.
    - profile.html: User profile view and edit page.

- static/
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets and images.
    - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
    - images/: Folder for dish images and other graphical assets used in the UI.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
    - users.txt: User information.
    - menu.txt: Menu items data.
    - reservations.txt: Reservation records.
    - waitlist.txt: Waitlist entries.
    - reviews.txt: User reviews.

This structure keeps backend logic centralized in one Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity. The data directory ensures organized local storage of all persistent data in the required pipe-delimited text format.
